doc.after: The earliest traces of human life in the area now known as Argentina are dated from the Paleolithic period with further traces in the Mesolithic and Neolithic 10 Until the period of European colonization Argentina was relatively sparsely populated by a wide number of diverse cultures with different social organizations 29 which can be divided into three main groups 30
